Algorithm Deconstruction Challenge
Task Priority Sorting & Filtering

Algorithm Overview
The task_priority.py file contains a weighted scoring algorithm that determines which tasks deserve the most attention. Instead of sorting by a single factor like priority level, it combines five different factors into one score, then ranks tasks from highest to lowest.

The Three Functions
Function	Purpose
calculate_task_score(task)	Gives each task a points total based on 5 factors
sort_tasks_by_importance(tasks)	Sorts all tasks from highest score to lowest
get_top_priority_tasks(tasks, limit=5)	Returns only the top N tasks from the sorted list

